column1: Title: Habitat and predator heterogeneity influence density of a declining mammal. Habitat composition (2015–2022) used in the density modelling of hedgehogs at Brackenhurst, Southwell, England. X and Y indicate the longitude/1000 and latitude/1000 (EPSG:27700) of the centroid of the 50 x 50 m grid cell, respectively; d2build and d2badger indicate euclidean distance (m) from the centroid of the 50 x 50 m grid cell to the nearest building and to the nearest badger sett, respectively; edge_length refers to edge density, the total length (m) of all types of edges within each  50 x 50 m grid cell. BUILDING, BADGER, and EDGE indicate the standardised z-score values of d2build,  d2badger, and edge_length, respectively. SOIL: Soil types (categorical: type 0, low permeability, and type 1, high permeability). LANDUSE: Land use (categorical: 0, arable; 1, amenity; 2, pasture).
